1
00:00:07,500 --> 00:00:08,208
So scary!

2
00:00:08,208 --> 00:00:10,000
What just happened?

3
00:00:12,208 --> 00:00:15,916
[eerie sound]

4
00:00:26,166 --> 00:00:28,625
It looks like everyone
came back to life.

5
00:00:28,833 --> 00:00:30,333
- Yeah.
- Crazy.

6
00:00:30,541 --> 00:00:33,333
But we all resonated with
Haumea and chose despair,

7
00:00:33,541 --> 00:00:36,000
so it's not like
we should be happy.

8
00:00:36,208 --> 00:00:37,875
All we can do is
watch over her.

9
00:00:38,083 --> 00:00:40,583
She still gets to make
her own choice.

10
00:00:43,708 --> 00:00:46,916
EPISODE 25"HERO'S TALE"

11
00:00:52,458 --> 00:00:54,333
[HAUMEA]
Why are you doing this?

12
00:00:54,541 --> 00:00:56,583
It will happen all over again.

13
00:00:56,791 --> 00:00:59,625
Despair will gather once more,
and another Great Cataclysm

14
00:00:59,625 --> 00:01:00,833
will begin.

15
00:01:01,041 --> 00:01:03,291
We fought so hard
to escape hell.

16
00:01:03,500 --> 00:01:06,041
All you've done is cause
our suffering to continue.

17
00:01:06,250 --> 00:01:08,333
No, it's not like that.

18
00:01:08,541 --> 00:01:10,875
And what makes this time
any different?

19
00:01:11,083 --> 00:01:12,416
As long as human life exists,

20
00:01:12,625 --> 00:01:15,625
the fear of death
can never be escaped.

21
00:01:15,625 --> 00:01:17,833
Our consciousness
creates despair.

22
00:01:18,041 --> 00:01:19,625
That's how it will always be.

23
00:01:19,833 --> 00:01:21,208
I can't disagree.

24
00:01:21,416 --> 00:01:22,750
Then tell me why.

25
00:01:22,958 --> 00:01:24,458
Because I changed things.

26
00:01:24,666 --> 00:01:25,583
It's better now.

27
00:01:25,791 --> 00:01:27,166
What do you mean?

28
00:01:27,375 --> 00:01:29,458
What exactly did you change?

29
00:01:31,458 --> 00:01:34,166
[HAJIKI] Something
feels kind of different.

30
00:01:34,375 --> 00:01:35,208
Is it me?

31
00:01:35,416 --> 00:01:37,708
Hajiki, you're back!

32
00:01:37,916 --> 00:01:40,291
I'm so happy!

33
00:01:43,750 --> 00:01:45,291
Oh, no!

34
00:01:45,500 --> 00:01:47,875
You're way too big to just
glomp people out of nowhere.

35
00:01:47,875 --> 00:01:50,416
Hold up, what happened to me?

36
00:01:50,625 --> 00:01:52,333
Oh, you're freaking me out.

37
00:01:52,541 --> 00:01:54,416
Oh, my arm grew back.

38
00:01:54,625 --> 00:01:57,333
Now I'm freaking
myself out! [screaming]

39
00:01:57,541 --> 00:01:58,875
What's going on?

40
00:01:59,083 --> 00:02:00,291
This is madness.

41
00:02:00,500 --> 00:02:01,625
Oh, jeez.

42
00:02:01,833 --> 00:02:03,708
I guess there's only
one explanation.

43
00:02:03,916 --> 00:02:05,000
Am I dead?

44
00:02:05,208 --> 00:02:06,416
I don't remember.

45
00:02:06,416 --> 00:02:08,708
Could you guys tell me
if I died or not?

46
00:02:08,916 --> 00:02:11,041
Yes, and I'm the one
who killed you.

47
00:02:11,041 --> 00:02:12,416
Uh-huh.

48
00:02:12,625 --> 00:02:13,875
I think it's starting
to come back to me now.

49
00:02:14,083 --> 00:02:15,458
When we first met, right?

50
00:02:15,666 --> 00:02:16,583
Indeed.

51
00:02:16,791 --> 00:02:18,166
I struck quickly.

52
00:02:18,375 --> 00:02:19,458
I see.

53
00:02:20,875 --> 00:02:22,166
It's fine.

54
00:02:22,375 --> 00:02:24,750
I can't sweat the small
stuff, you know.

55
00:02:24,958 --> 00:02:26,208
How is he so cute?

56
00:02:26,583 --> 00:02:28,875
AND THEN?

57
00:02:29,833 --> 00:02:31,291
- I'm Orochi.
- Yeah?

58
00:02:31,500 --> 00:02:32,291
Nice to meet you.

59
00:02:32,500 --> 00:02:34,291
I'm Hajiki.

60
00:02:34,500 --> 00:02:36,750
Killing him isn't
a deal breaker, huh?

61
00:02:36,750 --> 00:02:38,625
This is quite strange.

62
00:02:38,833 --> 00:02:40,291
Last I remember,
I was being burned

63
00:02:40,500 --> 00:02:42,041
to death by a black flame.

64
00:02:42,041 --> 00:02:45,458
I got my life and arm back,
even if it doesn't stay on.

65
00:02:45,458 --> 00:02:47,500
Hmm.

66
00:02:47,708 --> 00:02:48,750
Oh, well.

67
00:02:48,750 --> 00:02:49,750
Works for me.

68
00:02:49,958 --> 00:02:51,916
[scream]

69
00:02:52,125 --> 00:02:53,500
Captain!

70
00:02:53,708 --> 00:02:55,583
Maki, what's wrong with me?

71
00:02:55,791 --> 00:02:57,166
- Your neck!
- Oh, my.

72
00:02:57,166 --> 00:02:58,583
It's, uh--

73
00:02:59,583 --> 00:03:01,958
PEEL

74
00:03:05,041 --> 00:03:08,625
When I came to, my neck felt
weak, but I didn't know why.

75
00:03:08,833 --> 00:03:09,750
Try flexing it.

76
00:03:09,750 --> 00:03:11,208
Hell, yeah!

77
00:03:14,291 --> 00:03:15,458
Something isn't right.

78
00:03:15,666 --> 00:03:17,708
Everyone is far too laid back.

79
00:03:17,916 --> 00:03:20,291
For a second there, I thought
I was the only one who noticed.

80
00:03:20,500 --> 00:03:22,000
Everything feels off.

81
00:03:22,208 --> 00:03:23,458
The world has changed.

82
00:03:23,458 --> 00:03:26,041
It's formed from
a whole new image.

83
00:03:26,041 --> 00:03:27,750
Depending on your perspective,

84
00:03:27,958 --> 00:03:30,833
this could be pure madness.

85
00:03:35,583 --> 00:03:37,416
[HAUMEA] I don't understand.

86
00:03:37,625 --> 00:03:40,625
What could you possibly have
done to conquer despair?

87
00:03:40,833 --> 00:03:43,416
I resurrected the world,
but made one big change.

88
00:03:43,625 --> 00:03:45,583
I made life just
a little less precious.

89
00:03:45,791 --> 00:03:47,875
But what does
that accomplish?

90
00:03:47,875 --> 00:03:51,583
You said that when the value of
each person's soul increased,

91
00:03:51,791 --> 00:03:54,166
so did their fear of dying.

92
00:03:54,166 --> 00:03:56,416
So I changed death.

93
00:03:56,625 --> 00:03:58,458
Now, it's something
a little more familiar,

94
00:03:58,666 --> 00:04:01,333
maybe even friendly.

95
00:04:04,416 --> 00:04:07,000
[HAUMEA] And you think that
will bring an end to despair?

96
00:04:07,000 --> 00:04:09,041
I'll let you decide
if you want to start over

97
00:04:09,250 --> 00:04:10,916
in this world or not.

98
00:04:11,125 --> 00:04:13,833
If you think it's that bad,
I'll turn everything here

99
00:04:14,041 --> 00:04:16,000
to dust and do it over again.

100
00:04:16,000 --> 00:04:18,625
But why don't you
try enjoying life?

101
00:04:25,750 --> 00:04:28,125
She's going to choose
despair again.

102
00:04:28,333 --> 00:04:31,166
Brother, it's like the tale
of when the sun hid in a cave.

103
00:04:31,375 --> 00:04:32,875
Have a little faith.

104
00:04:33,083 --> 00:04:34,208
What's this?

105
00:04:52,208 --> 00:04:54,708
I'm here, it's Charon.

106
00:04:57,166 --> 00:05:00,166
Do you still hear
the voices of despair?

107
00:05:00,375 --> 00:05:02,583
I know the agony that
lives inside humanity's

108
00:05:02,791 --> 00:05:03,958
collective unconscious.

109
00:05:03,958 --> 00:05:05,500
I've felt their suffering
through you,

110
00:05:05,708 --> 00:05:07,291
Haumea, many times.

111
00:05:07,291 --> 00:05:10,291
But to tell you the truth,
that never troubled me,

112
00:05:10,500 --> 00:05:12,583
no matter how much despair
they felt.

113
00:05:12,791 --> 00:05:15,000
I didn't care about them
because the suffering

114
00:05:15,000 --> 00:05:17,291
you went through hurt me
more than the suffering

115
00:05:17,291 --> 00:05:19,166
of everyone else combined.

116
00:05:19,375 --> 00:05:22,625
That's why I wanted to start
the Great Cataclysm so quickly,

117
00:05:22,833 --> 00:05:25,000
not for mankind,
but to set you free

118
00:05:25,000 --> 00:05:27,416
from all of that pain.

119
00:05:27,416 --> 00:05:28,708
Or that's what I thought.

120
00:05:28,916 --> 00:05:30,416
But even then,
there was one regret

121
00:05:30,625 --> 00:05:31,916
I couldn't seem to shake.

122
00:05:33,000 --> 00:05:34,916
I didn't want to die

123
00:05:35,125 --> 00:05:38,041
because I had never once
seen you smile, Haumea.

124
00:05:38,250 --> 00:05:40,583
Every day,
you were always crying

125
00:05:40,791 --> 00:05:42,416
from the depths of your heart.

126
00:05:42,625 --> 00:05:44,166
The world's end
may be the climax,

127
00:05:44,375 --> 00:05:46,333
but that doesn't mean
you have to crymax too.

128
00:05:46,541 --> 00:05:47,250
PFFT

129
00:05:47,500 --> 00:05:48,750
That was a good one.

130
00:05:48,958 --> 00:05:51,458
If you don't want to smile,
that's fine.

131
00:05:51,666 --> 00:05:54,750
But please show me
your face at least.

132
00:05:57,833 --> 00:05:59,500
[HAUMEA] This isn't fair.

133
00:05:59,708 --> 00:06:02,458
Shinra Bansho,

134
00:06:02,666 --> 00:06:05,708
using Charon against me?

135
00:06:10,000 --> 00:06:11,625
You cheater.

136
00:06:12,583 --> 00:06:14,750
She's too cute.

137
00:06:25,166 --> 00:06:26,416
It's all right.

138
00:06:33,875 --> 00:06:35,833
It's a new beginning
for us all.

139
00:06:35,833 --> 00:06:39,458
It's a new world--
new me and new you.

140
00:06:39,666 --> 00:06:42,916
There's absolutely
no such thing as absolutes.

141
00:06:43,125 --> 00:06:45,916
But I absolutely swear
you won't regret this.

142
00:06:46,125 --> 00:06:49,708
You'll be glad you were born
into the world of death.

143
00:06:49,916 --> 00:06:51,333
Just trust me.

144
00:06:51,541 --> 00:06:54,291
You want me to abandon
the collective unconscious

145
00:06:54,291 --> 00:06:56,291
and enjoy my life?

146
00:06:56,500 --> 00:06:57,708
It's as simple as that?

147
00:06:57,708 --> 00:06:58,875
Simple as that.

148
00:06:59,083 --> 00:07:00,208
But I can't.

149
00:07:00,208 --> 00:07:02,708
There's still
so much despair left.

150
00:07:03,708 --> 00:07:05,625
Where will it go?

151
00:07:21,916 --> 00:07:24,708
It's never going
to catch on in this world.

152
00:07:30,125 --> 00:07:31,833
Time for you to go.

153
00:07:36,750 --> 00:07:39,125
Now get out there
and live again.

154
00:07:44,583 --> 00:07:45,916
Who could have ever guessed

155
00:07:46,125 --> 00:07:49,125
that Haumea would choose
to live after all?

156
00:07:49,125 --> 00:07:51,291
So what's next?

157
00:07:51,500 --> 00:07:53,000
All the despair
was washed away,

158
00:07:53,000 --> 00:07:54,750
so I suppose I'll go with it.

159
00:07:54,958 --> 00:07:56,750
- I think I'll choose oblivion.
- Amaterasu!

160
00:07:56,958 --> 00:07:59,833
Going back to life after all
these years would feel wrong.

161
00:08:00,041 --> 00:08:01,708
You don't mean that.

162
00:08:01,916 --> 00:08:03,333
I'm the doppelganger.

163
00:08:03,333 --> 00:08:05,250
I shouldn't get to stay alive
while you fade away.

164
00:08:05,458 --> 00:08:06,708
That's nonsense.

165
00:08:06,916 --> 00:08:09,000
No matter what happened,
your eyes were

166
00:08:09,000 --> 00:08:11,208
always brimming with hope.

167
00:08:11,416 --> 00:08:13,583
Even your decision
to choose death with us

168
00:08:13,791 --> 00:08:15,000
was only
because of the sympathy

169
00:08:15,208 --> 00:08:16,916
you had for me and Haumea.

170
00:08:17,125 --> 00:08:21,750
Iris, please, choose life
and live on in my stead--

171
00:08:23,708 --> 00:08:26,541
Or rather, live life enough
for me too.

172
00:08:26,750 --> 00:08:29,000
Even though
I'm nothing but a fake?

173
00:08:29,208 --> 00:08:30,500
What about you?

174
00:08:30,708 --> 00:08:33,625
I lived through the time
before the Cataclysm

175
00:08:33,833 --> 00:08:36,125
and through the world
of flames as well.

176
00:08:36,125 --> 00:08:38,166
Now, in the world of death
and souls,

177
00:08:38,375 --> 00:08:39,833
I can live once more?

178
00:08:39,833 --> 00:08:42,541
I don't think anyone, even me,
needs to exist

179
00:08:42,750 --> 00:08:44,000
across three realities.

180
00:08:44,208 --> 00:08:45,291
Fair point.

181
00:08:50,875 --> 00:08:52,958
Wait, before I go,

182
00:08:53,166 --> 00:08:55,625
I want to thank you for shining
your light on all of us--

183
00:08:55,833 --> 00:08:57,833
on the whole world.

184
00:08:58,041 --> 00:08:59,750
You're not a fake, Iris.

185
00:08:59,958 --> 00:09:02,833
In fact, you're the me
I always wanted to become.

186
00:09:27,666 --> 00:09:29,625
I'm so glad you're OK.

187
00:09:29,833 --> 00:09:30,708
Glad to be here.

188
00:09:30,916 --> 00:09:32,958
I'm back too, you know.

189
00:09:33,166 --> 00:09:35,000
Thanks for giving
this world a try.

190
00:09:35,208 --> 00:09:37,708
Well, I tried death first,
but it wasn't much fun at all.

191
00:09:37,916 --> 00:09:38,750
Good.

192
00:09:38,958 --> 00:09:40,208
You've finally done it.

193
00:09:40,416 --> 00:09:41,958
It was a hard-won victory.

194
00:09:42,166 --> 00:09:44,458
No, this isn't over yet.

195
00:09:49,125 --> 00:09:51,416
Your lives are
an abomination.

196
00:09:51,625 --> 00:09:52,916
They cannot continue.

197
00:09:53,125 --> 00:09:54,500
Death shall claim them.

198
00:09:54,708 --> 00:09:55,916
Huh?
That's no fair.

199
00:09:56,125 --> 00:09:57,125
We just came back to life.

200
00:09:57,125 --> 00:09:59,666
Brother,
what is this creature?

201
00:09:59,875 --> 00:10:01,625
It's the last piece of
the puzzle this world needs

202
00:10:01,833 --> 00:10:04,208
if we want to survive.

203
00:10:04,416 --> 00:10:05,875
He's our god.

204
00:10:06,083 --> 00:10:07,666
It looks a bit creepy to me.

205
00:10:07,666 --> 00:10:11,583
People make up gods and use
them as an excuse to be cruel.

206
00:10:11,791 --> 00:10:13,666
So I beat 'em to it
and made a real one.

207
00:10:13,875 --> 00:10:16,416
I wanted a god
that was irrefutable,

208
00:10:16,625 --> 00:10:18,958
so I manifested this guy
into our world--

209
00:10:19,166 --> 00:10:20,541
a god who rules over death.

210
00:10:20,750 --> 00:10:22,666
It's a skull.

211
00:10:22,875 --> 00:10:23,750
Yeah, it is.

212
00:10:23,958 --> 00:10:26,041
All right, God, we're ready.

213
00:10:26,250 --> 00:10:27,958
We will accept your judgment.

214
00:10:28,166 --> 00:10:30,458
That is a fine attitude.

215
00:10:30,666 --> 00:10:32,000
Now die.

216
00:10:36,458 --> 00:10:38,541
I won't be
needing it anymore.

217
00:10:47,666 --> 00:10:50,333
The powers that
you possess were far too great

218
00:10:50,541 --> 00:10:51,833
for any human.

219
00:10:51,833 --> 00:10:54,500
Therefore,
I retrieve them from you.

220
00:10:54,708 --> 00:10:57,500
I can see seven powers
with you.

221
00:10:57,708 --> 00:10:59,333
Are they the Adolla Bursts?

222
00:10:59,541 --> 00:11:02,083
How can that be when there
are only five pillars present?

223
00:11:02,291 --> 00:11:03,833
I'm God.

224
00:11:03,833 --> 00:11:06,416
I can retrieve them from those
who are not here as well.

225
00:11:07,750 --> 00:11:10,416
Some weird light
just came out of me.

226
00:11:10,625 --> 00:11:11,958
Something bothering you?

227
00:11:12,166 --> 00:11:14,958
Although I could not retrieve
the eighth one

228
00:11:15,166 --> 00:11:16,708
since it's not on this planet.

229
00:11:16,916 --> 00:11:18,458
Even God has his limits.

230
00:11:19,041 --> 00:11:20,291
FOOLS

231
00:11:23,125 --> 00:11:24,125
Ow!

232
00:11:24,333 --> 00:11:25,416
Why'd you flick me?

233
00:11:25,625 --> 00:11:27,000
Did you not predict that?

234
00:11:27,208 --> 00:11:27,958
Hang on.

235
00:11:28,166 --> 00:11:29,541
I didn't see it, no.

236
00:11:29,750 --> 00:11:31,000
I don't have everyone's
thoughts going

237
00:11:31,208 --> 00:11:32,500
through my head either.

238
00:11:33,958 --> 00:11:36,333
I don't have ignition
powers anymore?

239
00:11:36,541 --> 00:11:38,708
It's not just
all you pillars.

240
00:11:38,916 --> 00:11:41,458
It seems as though
I've lost my powers as well.

241
00:11:41,666 --> 00:11:43,083
So could that mean--

242
00:11:44,291 --> 00:11:46,583
[ALL] There's no more
spontaneous human combustion

243
00:11:46,791 --> 00:11:48,291
in our world?

244
00:11:48,291 --> 00:11:51,958
Well, then, I suppose I'll
go ahead and disappear now.

245
00:11:52,166 --> 00:11:53,625
Thanks for everything.

246
00:11:53,833 --> 00:11:55,416
And just where
exactly will you go?

247
00:11:55,625 --> 00:11:58,416
It'll be somewhere
you'd expect gods to be.

248
00:11:58,625 --> 00:12:00,583
I'll create a place with
the appropriate vibe

249
00:12:00,791 --> 00:12:01,833
and stay there.

250
00:12:01,833 --> 00:12:03,625
But if anything happens,
summon me.

251
00:12:03,833 --> 00:12:08,333
Reach me at 4242564.

252
00:12:08,541 --> 00:12:10,583
Toodle-oo!

253
00:12:10,791 --> 00:12:11,916
Wait!

254
00:12:12,125 --> 00:12:13,541
Uh.

255
00:12:13,541 --> 00:12:16,750
Why am I sensing this
overwhelmingly relaxed aura?

256
00:12:17,750 --> 00:12:20,083
It's fun, don't you think?
Or not?

257
00:12:20,291 --> 00:12:22,208
Well, I don't believe
it's a bad thing.

258
00:12:22,416 --> 00:12:24,416
Both of you
have done so well.

259
00:12:24,625 --> 00:12:26,666
I'm so proud of you.

260
00:12:26,875 --> 00:12:28,166
She's still in that form.

261
00:12:28,375 --> 00:12:29,750
I know.

262
00:12:29,958 --> 00:12:32,791
I don't look very
motherly like this,

263
00:12:33,000 --> 00:12:35,291
but the world is different now.

264
00:12:35,500 --> 00:12:37,833
Appearances aren't the same
kind of issue, are they?

265
00:12:38,041 --> 00:12:40,416
Excuse me,
are you Shinra's mother?

266
00:12:40,625 --> 00:12:41,833
Yes, that'd be me.

267
00:12:41,833 --> 00:12:44,750
I'm Inca,
and this little cutie is Iris.

268
00:12:44,958 --> 00:12:46,541
We're Shinra's girlfriends.

269
00:12:46,750 --> 00:12:48,041
Say what now?

270
00:12:48,250 --> 00:12:49,666
What are you talking about?

271
00:12:49,875 --> 00:12:52,708
You're dating both of them?

272
00:12:52,916 --> 00:12:54,083
You've got the wrong idea.

273
00:12:54,291 --> 00:12:56,125
[INCA]
Oh, it's all right, mama.

274
00:12:56,333 --> 00:12:58,833
Shinra's the superhero who
saved the entire world.

275
00:12:59,041 --> 00:13:00,750
He can have
a girlfriend or three.

276
00:13:00,958 --> 00:13:03,333
I don't even care
which number I am.

277
00:13:03,541 --> 00:13:07,000
Is that how you feel
about it too, Shinra?

278
00:13:07,208 --> 00:13:10,291
Well, anyway, now that
things have settled down,

279
00:13:10,500 --> 00:13:12,500
why don't we go meet up
with the rest of the 8th?

280
00:13:12,708 --> 00:13:14,250
Sounds good to me.

281
00:13:22,708 --> 00:13:25,625
[SHINRA]
Using knowledge from
people like Licht and Vulcan,

282
00:13:25,833 --> 00:13:27,458
we rebuilt the world.

283
00:13:27,666 --> 00:13:29,375
Almost.

284
00:13:29,583 --> 00:13:31,458
I mean, a lot of things
are very different

285
00:13:31,666 --> 00:13:34,208
from how they used to be.

286
00:13:34,416 --> 00:13:37,000
But you've still got
a place to come home to.

287
00:13:38,750 --> 00:13:42,291
I'll be waiting for you,
old buddy.

288
00:13:50,375 --> 00:13:53,791
Special Fire Force Company 8,
fire soldier Shinra Kusakabe

289
00:13:54,000 --> 00:13:55,291
reporting back from duty.

290
00:13:55,500 --> 00:13:57,958
The flames of spontaneous
human combustion

291
00:13:58,166 --> 00:13:59,750
have all been extinguished.

292
00:14:09,583 --> 00:14:11,583
I don't know
when it started,

293
00:14:11,791 --> 00:14:14,708
but instead of tension
forcing my smile,

294
00:14:14,916 --> 00:14:18,125
now, I do it naturally.

295
00:14:18,333 --> 00:14:20,166
No, I do know.

296
00:14:20,375 --> 00:14:23,541
It's when the boy called
"devil" found hope.

297
00:14:24,708 --> 00:14:27,583
The same day I joined the 8th.

298
00:14:28,875 --> 00:14:30,875
And I'm still smiling.

299
00:14:31,083 --> 00:14:33,000
FIRE FORCE

300
00:14:34,875 --> 00:14:38,208
FIRE FORCE
THE END

301
00:14:39,833 --> 00:14:43,000
[Japanese music]

302
00:14:43,208 --> 00:14:50,333
♪ ♪

303
00:16:03,750 --> 00:16:07,000
FIRE FORCE

304
00:16:09,750 --> 00:16:12,333
EPILOGUE

305
00:16:15,416 --> 00:16:17,083
[TAKERU gasps]

306
00:16:17,291 --> 00:16:19,291
[TAMAKI] It's kind of hard to
believe that there are cities

307
00:16:19,500 --> 00:16:21,208
like this outside of Tokyo.

308
00:16:21,416 --> 00:16:23,291
I guess this is how
the world used to be

309
00:16:23,500 --> 00:16:25,041
before the Great Cataclysm.

310
00:16:25,250 --> 00:16:27,083
No human combustion
now either.

311
00:16:27,291 --> 00:16:29,583
It's so peaceful,
it feels unreal.

312
00:16:34,083 --> 00:16:36,541
[TAKERU] Being on a date
with you feels unreal to me.

313
00:16:36,750 --> 00:16:38,875
I've never been this happy.

314
00:16:41,958 --> 00:16:43,666
I guess it's not that bad.

315
00:16:43,875 --> 00:16:45,708
Oh, dear.

316
00:16:45,916 --> 00:16:48,375
I wonder how everyone's
doing now that the Fire Force

317
00:16:48,583 --> 00:16:50,000
has been disbanded.

318
00:16:50,000 --> 00:16:52,250
From what I hear, they've
been doing expeditions.

319
00:16:52,458 --> 00:16:54,750
Nobody has ignition
powers anymore.

320
00:16:54,958 --> 00:16:57,458
But they say that some people
have gotten even stronger.

321
00:16:57,666 --> 00:16:59,166
The ones with
crazy strong souls

322
00:16:59,375 --> 00:17:01,375
are extra scary these days.

323
00:17:03,041 --> 00:17:04,083
WORLD HERO FORCE,

324
00:17:04,291 --> 00:17:05,833
COMMANDER-IN-CHIEF
OBI AKITARU

325
00:17:06,041 --> 00:17:08,500
They say Captain
Commander Obi can practically

326
00:17:08,708 --> 00:17:10,000
flip a mountain with one hand.

327
00:17:10,208 --> 00:17:11,833
And that's not all.

328
00:17:11,833 --> 00:17:15,000
The ones who are stronger than
him, those guys leveled up too.

329
00:17:16,625 --> 00:17:17,625
AIDE TO
THE HIGH BATTLE COMMANDER

330
00:17:17,833 --> 00:17:18,625
SAGAMIYA KONRO

331
00:17:18,833 --> 00:17:19,958
WORLD HERO FORCE,

332
00:17:19,958 --> 00:17:21,333
HIGH BATTLE COMMANDER
SHINMON BENIMARU

333
00:17:23,083 --> 00:17:24,625
I wonder what they're doing.

334
00:17:24,833 --> 00:17:26,500
Like, what's the point
of the expedition?

335
00:17:26,708 --> 00:17:28,833
There's way more
to the new world than Tokyo,

336
00:17:29,041 --> 00:17:30,541
so they're exploring.

337
00:17:31,375 --> 00:17:32,791
Commander in Chief Obi,

338
00:17:33,000 --> 00:17:35,958
we pinpointed the location
of that giant monster.

339
00:17:36,166 --> 00:17:37,958
It's been wild
since that day.

340
00:17:38,166 --> 00:17:41,291
So, of course, we're after
some huge 100-meter snake.

341
00:17:41,500 --> 00:17:44,250
Shinra cooked up a doozy
when he remade this world.

342
00:17:44,458 --> 00:17:46,750
Speaking of, where are
Shinra and the others?

343
00:17:46,958 --> 00:17:50,041
They're scouting about
20 kilometers ahead.

344
00:17:50,250 --> 00:17:51,333
Rekka.

345
00:17:51,541 --> 00:17:52,833
Thanks, guys, for real.

346
00:17:52,833 --> 00:17:55,833
You're off duty today,
so I appreciate this.

347
00:17:56,041 --> 00:17:57,708
The main force has things
covered for us.

348
00:17:57,916 --> 00:17:59,416
So you're actually
really going to go?

349
00:17:59,625 --> 00:18:02,708
I'll be setting out
into our great big new world,

350
00:18:02,916 --> 00:18:05,333
starting my journey
to master martial arts.

351
00:18:07,041 --> 00:18:08,833
Shinra's doing it again, huh?

352
00:18:09,041 --> 00:18:10,166
That's right.

353
00:18:10,166 --> 00:18:12,416
He's gone out chasing
after her again.

354
00:18:12,625 --> 00:18:15,083
Seeing my favorite
be so popular with the ladies

355
00:18:15,291 --> 00:18:17,000
makes me feel so giddy inside.

356
00:18:17,208 --> 00:18:18,000
Seriously?

357
00:18:18,208 --> 00:18:19,500
Hold on a second.

358
00:18:19,500 --> 00:18:21,333
Didn't you have a massive
crush on him too?

359
00:18:21,541 --> 00:18:23,916
Shinra is my favorite
no matter what he does.

360
00:18:24,125 --> 00:18:27,250
And as his hardcore fan,
I have to forgive him, right?

361
00:18:27,458 --> 00:18:29,291
I'm not sure
it works like that.

362
00:18:29,500 --> 00:18:31,291
He's the entire
world's hero now,

363
00:18:31,500 --> 00:18:35,041
so I do realize that I can't
keep him all to myself forever.

364
00:18:35,250 --> 00:18:38,041
At this point, it's not like
romance is everything to me.

365
00:18:38,250 --> 00:18:40,875
So I'm not going to get jealous
and upset over small stuff.

366
00:18:41,083 --> 00:18:42,291
That'd be silly.

367
00:18:42,291 --> 00:18:44,708
Shinra really is
something special, though.

368
00:18:47,416 --> 00:18:50,041
I hope he'll be
coming back home soon.

369
00:18:55,333 --> 00:18:57,916
The monster is on the other
side of that mountain, huh?

370
00:18:58,125 --> 00:19:00,291
From what I hear,
it's some kind of giant snake

371
00:19:00,500 --> 00:19:02,083
that's over 100 meters long.

372
00:19:02,291 --> 00:19:04,291
Sounds pretty crazy.

373
00:19:04,500 --> 00:19:07,333
Well, you turned this
into a crazy world, didn't you?

374
00:19:08,500 --> 00:19:10,708
It's a fun one, though.

375
00:19:10,916 --> 00:19:12,666
Where's Arthur and Excalibur?

376
00:19:12,875 --> 00:19:14,166
They're down at the foot
of the mountain.

377
00:19:14,375 --> 00:19:15,875
Some quick thing
to take care of.

378
00:19:16,083 --> 00:19:17,416
[SHINRA]
I guess we should go get him.

379
00:19:17,625 --> 00:19:20,166
I don't think he can
find his own way back.

380
00:19:20,375 --> 00:19:22,083
I mean, he was up
in space for a long time

381
00:19:22,291 --> 00:19:24,666
before he finally made it home.

382
00:19:24,875 --> 00:19:27,625
[adventurous music]

383
00:19:27,833 --> 00:19:34,500
♪ ♪

384
00:19:36,625 --> 00:19:39,041
Arthur, you about done here?

385
00:19:39,250 --> 00:19:41,625
Yeah, I've paid my respects.

386
00:19:41,833 --> 00:19:42,875
Good.

387
00:19:42,875 --> 00:19:45,041
So I'll be facing
a hydra, will I?

388
00:19:45,250 --> 00:19:46,708
Sounds exciting to me.

389
00:19:46,916 --> 00:19:49,000
Well, somebody might
actually die this time.

390
00:19:49,208 --> 00:19:50,833
Yeah, sounds rough to me.

391
00:19:51,041 --> 00:19:52,500
Ain't that right, Excalibur?

392
00:19:54,666 --> 00:19:56,125
You are going to die.

393
00:19:56,333 --> 00:19:57,750
I see the shadow
of death following you

394
00:19:57,958 --> 00:19:59,041
into the next world.

395
00:19:59,250 --> 00:20:00,333
Man, shut up.

396
00:20:00,333 --> 00:20:02,541
He somehow makes
Arthur seem normal.

397
00:20:02,750 --> 00:20:03,958
Well, we better
wrap this up quick

398
00:20:04,166 --> 00:20:06,166
and get Vice Commander
Hinawa back home.

399
00:20:06,375 --> 00:20:08,666
I don't want Maki's pops
getting mad at me.

400
00:20:08,875 --> 00:20:10,291
Her dad.

401
00:20:10,291 --> 00:20:12,791
You know, those two are
pretty clingy these days.

402
00:20:13,000 --> 00:20:15,250
No one really knows
what's going to happen next.

403
00:20:15,458 --> 00:20:17,375
So you just gotta go
for what you want.

404
00:20:17,583 --> 00:20:18,875
There's no time to waste.

405
00:20:20,500 --> 00:20:21,708
What about you?

406
00:20:21,916 --> 00:20:23,833
What did I just say?

407
00:20:24,041 --> 00:20:26,333
Hey, it's the dimwit trio.

408
00:20:26,541 --> 00:20:28,125
I was starting to worry.

409
00:20:28,125 --> 00:20:31,291
I was kind of afraid that you
would stop chasing after me.

410
00:20:31,500 --> 00:20:32,583
Inca?

411
00:20:32,583 --> 00:20:33,833
I should have known
you're the one

412
00:20:34,041 --> 00:20:35,708
who summoned that giant snake.

413
00:20:35,916 --> 00:20:38,875
So tell me, Shinra, have you
thought about what I asked you?

414
00:20:39,083 --> 00:20:40,375
There's no way in hell
that I'm going

415
00:20:40,583 --> 00:20:41,541
to give you what you want.

416
00:20:41,750 --> 00:20:42,666
But why?

417
00:20:42,666 --> 00:20:44,291
It's not cool to be so stingy.

418
00:20:44,500 --> 00:20:45,791
I just want your baby, Shinra.

419
00:20:46,000 --> 00:20:47,625
- That's all.
- Bow-wow-wow.

420
00:20:47,833 --> 00:20:49,625
Come on, you know
that I'm with Iris now.

421
00:20:49,833 --> 00:20:51,125
Huh?

422
00:20:51,333 --> 00:20:52,958
Listen, you are way too boring
for me to want

423
00:20:53,166 --> 00:20:54,208
to be with you like that, OK?

424
00:20:54,416 --> 00:20:55,250
Yucky.

425
00:20:55,458 --> 00:20:56,291
[SHINRA] What do you mean?

426
00:20:56,500 --> 00:20:57,916
I thought you loved me!

427
00:20:57,916 --> 00:20:59,958
The only thing I want is
for you to put a baby in me!

428
00:21:00,166 --> 00:21:02,041
Wh-- what are
you even saying?

429
00:21:02,250 --> 00:21:04,291
That's like,
such an insane thing to say.

430
00:21:04,500 --> 00:21:05,875
I'm not going to do
anything like that.

431
00:21:06,083 --> 00:21:07,125
Why not?

432
00:21:07,125 --> 00:21:08,250
All we need to do
is ask Licht,

433
00:21:08,458 --> 00:21:09,875
and I'm sure
he could make it happen.

434
00:21:10,083 --> 00:21:12,000
[SHINRA] That's not
exactly what I mean.

435
00:21:12,208 --> 00:21:13,583
[INCA] I want to have
the child of the hero

436
00:21:13,791 --> 00:21:15,375
who saved the world.

437
00:21:15,375 --> 00:21:18,083
You'll have more, so what's the
harm of letting me have one?

438
00:21:18,291 --> 00:21:19,166
You tell me.

439
00:21:19,375 --> 00:21:20,541
Why do you want one anyway?

440
00:21:20,750 --> 00:21:22,083
It's pretty simple, really.

441
00:21:22,291 --> 00:21:23,916
These days, we're
in a world based on death.

442
00:21:24,125 --> 00:21:25,833
And that means the value
of life is way different.

443
00:21:26,041 --> 00:21:28,083
So I'm just hoping to have
something that really

444
00:21:28,291 --> 00:21:30,458
connects me to the future.

445
00:21:33,583 --> 00:21:35,041
He saved the world too.

446
00:21:35,250 --> 00:21:37,125
I bet Arthur could
give you what you want.

447
00:21:37,333 --> 00:21:39,000
Hey, now,
don't pawn this off on me.

448
00:21:39,208 --> 00:21:40,000
No dummies, please.

449
00:21:40,208 --> 00:21:41,041
Ha!

450
00:21:41,250 --> 00:21:42,375
In your face, Shinra.

451
00:21:42,375 --> 00:21:43,791
She's talking
about you, you dummy.

452
00:21:44,000 --> 00:21:46,500
I've wanted to die
as long as I can remember.

453
00:21:46,708 --> 00:21:47,916
But since
you changed the world,

454
00:21:48,125 --> 00:21:49,541
I've actually
gotten into living.

455
00:21:49,541 --> 00:21:53,166
So thank you for saving
me in every possible way.

456
00:21:54,583 --> 00:21:55,958
And that's why
I want to continue

457
00:21:56,166 --> 00:21:58,000
your legacy with the baby.

458
00:21:58,208 --> 00:21:59,333
Can I, please?

459
00:21:59,541 --> 00:22:00,916
Hmm.

460
00:22:01,125 --> 00:22:01,916
I'm gonna say no.

461
00:22:02,125 --> 00:22:03,208
Ugh.

462
00:22:03,208 --> 00:22:04,750
After all this,
you're still no fun.

463
00:22:04,958 --> 00:22:06,958
Fine, until you say it's OK,

464
00:22:07,166 --> 00:22:08,500
I guess I'm going to keep
being a witch

465
00:22:08,708 --> 00:22:10,333
and causing some mayhem.

466
00:22:10,333 --> 00:22:12,375
Even though you're still such a
pill, this world you've created

467
00:22:12,583 --> 00:22:14,083
has been a real blast.

468
00:22:14,291 --> 00:22:15,916
So thanks for that, too, hero.

469
00:22:17,041 --> 00:22:18,291
Yeah, of course.

470
00:22:18,500 --> 00:22:21,625
[laughter]

471
00:22:39,250 --> 00:22:41,000
25 YEARS LATER

472
00:22:41,208 --> 00:22:42,583
[laughter fading]

473
00:22:45,333 --> 00:22:50,875
[music playing]

474
00:22:51,083 --> 00:22:52,166
WORLD HERO FORCE,

475
00:22:52,166 --> 00:22:53,208
SUPREME LEADER KUSAKABE SHINRA
[42]

476
00:22:53,416 --> 00:22:54,708
Good morning,
Supreme Commander.

477
00:22:54,916 --> 00:22:56,375
There's a message for you.

478
00:22:56,375 --> 00:22:58,916
President Obi has sent you
a congratulatory telegram.

479
00:22:59,125 --> 00:23:01,083
I'm happy he found time
in his busy schedule.

480
00:23:01,291 --> 00:23:04,250
And you've got family
joining the hero force.

481
00:23:04,458 --> 00:23:07,208
I won't lie and say
I'm not worried,

482
00:23:07,416 --> 00:23:09,416
but it's still very exciting.

483
00:23:10,750 --> 00:23:14,500
Live life passionately,
and you won't have any regrets.

484
00:23:14,708 --> 00:23:17,041
So death's not all
that big of a deal.

485
00:23:17,250 --> 00:23:18,666
Life's truly a gift.

486
00:23:18,875 --> 00:23:20,958
Let's be dumb
and have lots of fun.

487
00:23:21,166 --> 00:23:22,750
And with that
as our motto,

488
00:23:22,958 --> 00:23:25,666
our souls are going to burn
brighter than ever before.

489
00:23:26,791 --> 00:23:30,833
Let's see here, a child of God
in human form.

490
00:23:32,041 --> 00:23:34,958
How is this kid
going to turn out?

491
00:23:35,166 --> 00:23:36,458
I know.

492
00:23:36,458 --> 00:23:38,750
Let's start by making him
resemble the hero

493
00:23:38,958 --> 00:23:40,833
who saved the world
from despair.

494
00:23:41,041 --> 00:23:42,000
Yes!

495
00:23:42,208 --> 00:23:44,000
Hey, there kid.

496
00:23:44,208 --> 00:23:46,958
[Japanese singing]

497
00:23:47,166 --> 00:23:53,750
♪ ♪

498
00:23:55,125 --> 00:23:58,583
And so a new world
free from despair

499
00:23:58,791 --> 00:24:00,875
was created for all of us.

500
00:24:01,083 --> 00:24:03,833
[Japanese singing]

501
00:24:04,041 --> 00:24:05,625
♪ ♪
